Date: 15/5/1916
Source: Rangitikei Advocate
Author:
Vol / Page: 8
Edition:
Quote: The Derwent potato, for which North Otagowas at one time famous, has almostdisappeared. At time a tuber of thevariety is to be obtained, but it is apoor apology for the mealy, fullflavoured sort that was so abundantduring the year[s] 1864 to 1885. The lateMr. Hassal, of Cave Valley, brought themearly into prominence, and they weredistributed over Otago as the Cave Valleyflour balls.
